         <tbody><tr class=3D"replica" name=3D"intro">
          <td style=3D"padding-bottom: 36px;">
           <p style=3D"margin: 0; color: #000000; font-size: 16px; line-hei=
ght: 30px; margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 0;">Welcome to Wall Power, fina=
lly back in these United States. I=E2=80=99m <b>Marion Maneker</b>=E2=80=94=
ready to tell you about my Parisian sojourn.<br/><br/>Before embarking on t=
his fortnight abroad, we set out to answer two questions. First, would it b=
e London or Paris that proved to be ascendant, both in art fairs and auctio=
ns? Second, might the art market reverse its momentum? As it turns out, we =
were asking the wrong questions. <br/><br/>The pendulum has <i>already</i> =
switched directions. In Paris, I ran into a major private dealer at the <b>=
Tom Wesselmann </b>retrospective who was all smiles, reporting that many ga=
lleries had better sales in London than expected. That=E2=80=99s something =
I heard in a number of places. This same dealer also felt that a good showi=
ng in Paris=E2=80=94both at the fair and at the manicured auctions here=E2=
=80=94would set the table for November. If those
sales deliver, we could be in for a new market narrative. <br/><br/>Before =
getting into what happened at Art Basel Paris, however, let=E2=80=99s brief=
ly discuss where we <i>should </i>be turning our attention. Indeed, what=E2=
=80=99s going on in London is particular to the <i>London </i>market, which=
 is still absorbing the aftershocks of Brexit. Yet it remains a major art c=
enter, with numerous great museums, a recent history of strong production b=
y local artists, and an extensive gallery infrastructure. Also, American bu=
yers are currently sustaining the market. So London plays an obvious role; =
there=E2=80=99s a special relationship in art, too. That means the better q=
uestion isn=E2=80=99t whether London can withstand the ascent of Paris, but=
 whether Paris can efficiently consolidate the European art trade via large=
r and more efficiently centralized sales at the auction houses. More on tha=
t on Tuesday. Now I want to tell you more about Art Basel in Paris. <br/></=
p>
          </td>
         </tr>
