         <tr class=3D"replica" name=3D"s11">
          <td style=3D"padding-bottom: 36px; color: #000000; font-size: 16p=
x; line-height: 30px; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0;">This was the third =
year Art Basel has operated in Paris, but it was the first year that the fa=
ir has been called Art Basel. It was also the first time the fair has been =
held at the Grand Palais, which is more prominently located than the tempor=
ary space near the Eiffel Tower used in recent years. But I was left wonder=
ing what Art Basel can do to top this year, and whether the French cultural=
 establishment can continue to raise its level of offerings. There=E2=80=99=
s also the question of what the success of Art Basel Paris will mean for th=
e company=E2=80=99s other fairs. Many American collectors would prefer to s=
pend a week in Paris over a few days in Basel. One Midwestern collector tol=
d me he had arrived with his daughters and their spouses planning to spend =
a diary-packed week in Paris. But they did not buy anything at the fair=E2=
=80=94at least, not anything
serious. Horowitz would probably prefer that he go to Basel to buy and Pari=
s to have fun, anyway. But will he?  <br/><br/>And what about Miami? With e=
veryone gathered here in Paris in October, how important will it be to head=
 to Miami in December? I spoke to a gallerist from Switzerland who did Frie=
ze, and who held a show in their Paris apartment that involved a series of =
dinners and cocktail parties to consider the works. This gallery does eight=
 art fairs a year, but this gallerist was looking forward to Miami, too. So=
 maybe everything=E2=80=99s all right in the art fair ecosystem. <br/></td>
         </tr>
